summary><msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010105563 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002005579" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_908-item1"><textLang mainLang="fa">Persian </textLang><author><persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_8149912313906210668">Tamīz al-Dīn ibn Muḥammad Yāvar</persName><persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_8149912313906210668">تميز الدّين ابن محمّد ياور</persName></author><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22332">Būstān</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22332">بوستان</title><note><p>Autograph copy of a lexicon or farhang and commentary or sharḥ by <persName key="viaf_8149912313906210668" role="aut scr">Mawlavī Tamīz al-Dīn ibn Muḥammad Yāvar</persName> appended in margins around the bi-columnar arrangement of the mas̲navī, the <title key="work_22332">Būstān</title> of <persName key="viaf_73859635" role="ant">Shaykh Saʿdī Shīrāzī</persName>. 
                        </p><p>This copy, begun in Ramaz̤ān 1238/May 1823, was intended for lithography. 
</p><p>Dated colophon (f. 115r): completed probably in the hand of the author (Tamīz al-Dīn ibn Muḥammad Yāvar), for the <orgName>Maṭbaʿ Aysiyātik Līthūgrāfik Kanpī</orgName> (sic, <orgName>Asiatic Lithographic Company</orgName>), dār al-ḥukūmat <placeName>Calcutta</placeName>, 1244/1828. 
                        </p><p>Minute scribal nastaʿlīq, arranged in three vertical columns and a lower panel, two vertical columns for the Būstān, the third vertical column and the lower panel reserved for the lexicon and commentary. 
</p><p>Verses counted in accordance with the chapters or bāb. 
</p><p>Paginated in Persian, with stamped foliation. 
</p><p>Original covers lost. 
</p><p>Only front board remaining from later tooled leather covers (board delaminating revealing Kaithi accounts). 
</p></note></msItem></msContents><physDesc><objectDesc form="codex"><supportDesc material="chart"><extent>155 ff.<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm"><height>292</height><width>162</width></dimensions></extent></supportDesc></objectDesc><handDesc><handNote script="Arabic" scope="major" /></handDesc></physDesc><history><origin calendar="Hijri-qamari" when="1828" when-custom="1244"><placeName>Calcutta, Kalkattah</placeName><origPlace>India, Kolkata</origPlace></origin><provenance><p>Purchased by the Government of India at sale organised by Delhi Prize Agents, 1859; administrative deposit India Office Library, 1876 
